node.text:
In 2021, nearly 50% of internships were unpaid, according to a survey by the National Association of Colleges and Employers. These types of internships have proven to further inequity, giving opportunities to a select few while isolating others. So why are unpaid internships still so prevalent in our workforce today? 

Read more: https://cnb.cx/3AKBcBK

node.title: Here's why unpaid internships still exist in corporate America

node.text:
Steve, 39, and Courtney, 36, retired in 2016 with a combined net worth of $870,000. Watch as Kevin O'Leary, CNBC's new "Money Court" judge, shares his take on the couple's desert-dwelling lifestyle.

Read more: https://cnb.cx/2VLpkRj

node.title: Kevin O'Leary reacts to a millennial couple who retired early in their 30s

node.text:
Katie McRose, 26, and her wife Darian travel around Texas to sheer sheep, llamas and alpacas. They founded their business, Right Choice Shearing, in 2019. This year, they expect to bring in at least $80,000 servicing over 575 farms. 

Read more: https://cnb.cx/3AfkSJ2

node.title: Bringing in $80K a year shearing sheep in Texas.

node.text:
Alex Sanchez lives in Warrenville, Illinois, and makes $360,000 a year. While Alex is generally mindful of his spending, his business expenses add up. 

For one week, Alex tracked his spending to see where his money went.

Full interview: https://cnb.cx/2WnnaXU

node.title: What a 26-year-old making $360,000 a year spends in a week

node.text: More dads are choosing to stay at home with their kids. Will Covid-19 accelerate this trend?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 23, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Warren Buffett says these businesses do the best during periods of high inflation #makeit'.

node.text:
From used cars to gas to groceries, inflation continues raise the price of goods in the U.S. The consumer price index jumped 5.4% last month from where it was in July 2020, matching its biggest jump since 2008.⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, Warren Buffett breaks down why some businesses are more likely to succeed than others during periods of high inflation.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 23, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says ''James Bond' actor Daniel Craig says his children won't be receiving his multimillion-dollar fortune #makeit'.

node.text:
Daniel Craig may command eight-figure Hollywood paychecks, but the 53-year-old actor isn't planning on sharing much of it with his children.⁠
⁠
At the link in bio, Craig shared his philosophy on inheritance and why he finds it "distasteful" to leave heirs massive amounts of money.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 22, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, eyeglasses and text that says 'Silicon Valley veteran David Selinger on launching a $5 billion company, working for Jeff Bezos and lessons for success #makeit'.

node.text:
In total, David Selinger — an early Amazon employee, co-founder and CTO of Redfin and most recently, founder and CEO of home security start-up Deep Sentinel — has been a co-founder, early employee or an advisor at no fewer than 19 Silicon Valley start-ups.⁠
⁠
At the link in bio, he shares what it was like working for Jeff Bezos and his most important leadership lesson.

node.text:
The Gap is betting on Kanye West's influence to revive the brand. The collaboration could bring in nearly $1 billion in incremental sales in 2022, according to an analyst from Wells Fargo.

See more: https://cnb.cx/3AXUh3B

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How much money a single person needs to earn to get by in every U.S. state AK Living Wage Minimum ($USD) 30000 35000 40000 WA MT ME ND MN WI VT ID NH WY MI SD IA NY OR IL MA IN NV RI co oH NE PA NJ MO CA KY CT UT WV NM VA KS MD AR DE TN AZ NC OK SC HI LA DC MS AL GA TX FL Source: MIT Living Wage : Calculator #makeit'.

node.text:
For single people living in the U.S., earning enough money to make ends meet looks different for each person. ⁠
⁠
MIT's Living Wage Calculator estimates the minimum income necessary for a single person to cover living expenses and stay above the poverty line, without outside help, across the U.S.⁠
⁠
At the link in bio, we're sharing a closer look at what a living wage would be, before taxes, for a single person, including the estimated costs of housing and food, in every U.S. state.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 22, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'Author who studies millionaires: 240 minutes a day separates the rich from everyone else #makeit'.

node.text:
There are 1,440 minutes in each day. And most people, rich or poor, use about 1,200 of those minutes for the following activities: work, commuting, family-related, sleeping, eating, bathing, bathroom and dressing.⁠
⁠
That leaves about 240 minutes of time each day. And it is what the rich do with those 240 minutes that separates them from everyone else.⁠
⁠
So, what do they do? 🤔 Find out at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Forget dogecoin and meme stocks it's usually better to keep your money boring MOMHOHLAlo.co #makeit'.

node.text:
Cryptocurrencies, meme stocks and other buzzy financial products have captured the attention of many young investors.⁠
⁠
At the link in our bio, financial experts explain why they shouldn't come at the expense of other, more traditional investments.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 21, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people sitting, furniture and text that says 'This husband-and-wife team shares their tips for going into business together #makeit'.

node.text:
As the husband-and-wife team behind clothing rental app Style Theory, Raena Lim and Chris Halim are united not only in marriage, but also in business.⁠
⁠
Having spent five years perfecting their approach, the 32-year-old pair shared advice for other couple co-founders — both in and outside of business — at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'A Sha kung fu master shares the 5 mental states that hold us back in life and how to fight them #makeit'.

node.text:
One of the most important teachings is the “five hindrances of self-mastery.” These are the core mental states that prevent us from seeing clearly, making smart decisions, achieving our goals and living a happier, more harmonious life.⁠
⁠
From ill will to restlessness, a Shaolin kung fu master reveals the 5 mental states that hold us back in life, in the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 21, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, car, outdoors and text that says 'Here's what kind of car loan you can get depending on your credit score #make'.

node.text:
If you're shopping for a car and plan to finance your vehicle, you'll want to consider your credit history and credit scores. 🚗⁠
⁠
At the link in bio, we're sharing how you can position yourself to receive the best interest rate from an auto lender.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC Make It on August 20, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, eyeglasses and text that says 'Here's how much money each generation has saved for retirement #makeit'.

node.text:
When it comes to personal and retirement savings, millennials are firmly in the middle of the pack compared to other generations. ⁠
⁠
In a new study from Northwestern Mutual, more than 2,000 American adults were asked how much money they have saved for retirement. Curious where you fall? We're breaking down the average amounts saved for each generation at the link in bio. 💰
